# KITSUNE Subtitle Standards

## Required Reading

- Read `PROJECT_CONSTITUTION.md` before implementing features.
- Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` before making architectural decisions.
- Read `AI_RULES.md` before generating code.

## General Principles

- Never implement features that are not requested.
- Never invent architecture.
- Never duplicate existing logic.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Follow TypeScript best practices.
- Follow Rust best practices.
- Keep files under 400 lines whenever practical.
- UI components must not contain business logic; business logic belongs outside React components.
- Prefer reusable modules and descriptive names.
- Avoid utility dumping grounds (no catch-all `utils` files).
- Explain important implementation decisions.

## When Unsure

Ask instead of assuming.
